reviewText: Unfortunately wel did the outside circle road on the east, north and west for 1 week and did not see most of the things on the video.

The documentary takes you through the most fascinating places in Iceland with excellent narration and is not drowned out with background music. Iceland is shown in its beauty with waterfalls, volcanoes, geothermal activity like Yellowstone National Park, only it's everywhere and under your feet!!  Reykjavik is surprisingly beautiful as well.  The film; however, is only 30 minutes, but still worth your time and money.
I'm taking a group back to Iceland for New Year's and this is a great way to give people the feel of what they will experience.  If you love fireworks this is the place at New Year's!
What a great travel DVD this is. I do not like travel DVD's, but this one is great.
I was in Iceland for a weekend and this DVD was my guide, took the same trip as is on the DVD and loved it. Thumbs up for this high qualety travel DVD.Fantastic images
